<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_kʼæʒ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼæʒæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>кривой</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>crooked</q></cit></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ kænyn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сгибать</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>bend</q></cit></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ-mæʒ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>криво и косо</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>crooked and askew</q></cit></sense></re></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Очевидна связь с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kāz, kaj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/><w>kž-</w><gloss><q>кривой</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_BSOS"><biblScope>IX 84</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kaj-maj</w></mentioned> = ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/></xr>. Трудно сказать, имеем ли дело с исконным родством или заимствованием. Перебойным вариантом данного слова является <xr><ref target="#entry_xæʒ"/></xr>. Может быть, сюда же <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼæʒīl"/></xr> ‘хвост’.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Bailey._Asica"><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The connection with <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kāz, kaj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/><w>kž-</w><gloss><q>crooked</q></gloss></mentioned> is evident (<bibl corresp="#ref_BSOS"><biblScope>IX 84</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kaj-maj</w></mentioned> = Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/></xr>. It is difficult to say whether it is the congation or the borrowing. The irregularly corresponding variant of this word is <xr><ref target="#entry_xæʒ"/></xr>. Maybe, <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼæʒīl"/></xr> ‘tail’ is related to it as well.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Bailey._Asica"><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><note type="internal">перебойный вариант??</note></entry>